    "body": "fix https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/54\r\n\r\n\r\nThis commit updates `ostd/src/arch/miri/mm/mod.rs` to remove direct architecture-specific operations (especially ones that rely on x86 register/assembly paths) in the Miri build path.\r\n\r\nMain changes:\r\n- All TLB flush helpers are turned into no-ops in Miri:\r\n  - `tlb_flush_addr`\r\n  - `tlb_flush_addr_range`\r\n  - `tlb_flush_all_excluding_global`\r\n  - `tlb_flush_all_including_global`\r\n- Page-table switching no longer writes to `CR3` directly.\r\n  - `activate_page_table` now calls an external Miri hook: `kern_miri_set_root_page_table(root_paddr)`.\r\n  - The `root_pt_cache` parameter is now ignored (`_root_pt_cache`).\r\n- Current page-table lookup no longer reads `CR3` directly.\r\n  - `current_page_table_paddr` now calls `kern_miri_get_root_page_table()`.\r\n- Adds two `unsafe extern \"Rust\"` declarations for these Miri runtime hooks, with comments describing their expected behavior.\r\n\r\nNet effect:\r\n- The Miri memory-management path is simplified and decoupled from low-level x86 register manipulation/asm-related logic.",
